NAME
    gcloud alpha monitoring - manage Stackdriver Monitoring alerting policies,
        dashboards, and notification channels

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha monitoring GROUP [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Manage Stackdriver Monitoring alerting policies, dashboards, and
    notification channels.

    More information can be found here:
      o https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/api/v3/
      o https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/alerts/using-alerting-api
      o https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/alerts/using-channels-api
      o https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/dashboards/api-dashboard

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

GROUPS
    GROUP is one of the following:

     channel-descriptors
        (ALPHA) Read Stackdriver Monitoring notification channel descriptors.

     channels
        (ALPHA) Manage Stackdriver Monitoring notification channels.

     dashboards
        (ALPHA) Manage Stackdriver Monitoring dashboards.

     policies
        (ALPHA) Manage Stackdriver Monitoring alerting policies.

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. If this
    command fails with API permission errors despite specifying the right
    project, you may be trying to access an API with an invitation-only early
    access whitelist. These variants are also available:

        $ gcloud monitoring
        $ gcloud beta monitoring

